os-mouros-boardwalk",{"category":257,"date":34,"description":258,"mediaAsset":259,"title":263},{"name":13,"slug":14},"Boardwalk in Condeixa with recycled plastic structures, bridges, a viewpoint and signage integrated into a high-biodiversity ecosystem.",[260],{"alt":38,"extension":39,"height":67,"hotspot":38,"type":41,"uid":261,"url":262,"width":69},"aaaf1dd73db7","https://cdn.sanity.io/images/535lnz3g/production/8a74e4c9e383c63301038887fe37e5fade4991de-4304x2870.jpg","Rio dos Mouros boardwalk",{"metadata":265,"presentation":267},{"slug":266},"trail-cangosta-do-estevao",{"category":268,"date":269,"description":270,"mediaAsset":271,"title":276},{"name":13,"slug":14},"2025-09-10","Descubra soluções personalizadas de sinalética urbana para o Trilho da Cangosta do Estêvão com a Floema Urban. Inove seus espaços urbanos.",[272],{"alt":238,"extension":39,"height":273,"hotspot":38,"type":41,"uid":239,"url":274,"width":275},1158,"https://cdn.sanity.io/images/535lnz3g/production/ad76d301da209b284d6f595163142433b9255713-1752x1158.jpg",1752,"Trail Cangosta do Estêvão",{"name":16,"posts":278,"slug":17},[279,285,291,297,308],{"metadata":280,"presentation":281},{"slug":113},{"category":282,"date":116,"description":117,"mediaAsset":283,"title":122},{"name":16,"slug":17},[284],{"alt":38,"extension":39,"height":40,"hotspot":38,"type":41,"uid":120,"url":121,"width":44},{"metadata":286,"presentation":287},{"slug":125},{"category":288,"date":116,"description":128,"mediaAsset":289,"title":134},{"name":16,"slug":17},[290],{"alt":131,"extension":39,"height":40,"hotspot":38,"type":41,"uid":132,"url":133,"width":44},{"metadata":292,"presentation":293},{"slug":137},{"category":294,"date":116,"description":140,"mediaAsset":295,"title":145},{"name":16,"slug":17},[296],{"alt":38,"extension":39,"height":40,"hotspot":38,"type":41,"uid":143,"url":144,"width":44},{"metadata":298,"presentation":300},{"slug":299},"floema-replastic-en",{"category":301,"date":116,"description":302,"mediaAsset":303,"title":307},{"name":16,"slug":17},"What is waste today can become construction material. Floema RePlastic starts from post-consumer plastic and transforms it into permanent construction systems, capable of replacing conventional materials and reducing pressure on natural resources.",[304],{"alt":38,"extension":39,"height":40,"hotspot":38,"type":41,"uid":305,"url":306,"width":44},"bc6a76311dc5","https://cdn.sanity.io/images/535lnz3g/production/71a05d9e878eb1c610a88d33d55606c580cd07d0-2000x1333.jpg","Floema RePlastic — solutions in recycled plastic",{"metadata":309,"presentation":311},{"slug":310},"floema-urban-en",{"category":312,"date":116,"description":313,"mediaAsset":314,"title":318},{"name":16,"slug":17},"For decades, cities were designed for traffic and passage. Squares became empty, streets became transit corridors and many public spaces lost their dimension of encounter. Floema Urban intervenes in this territory. It develops and produces solutions that reorganise urban space, introduce legibility, create pauses and return to cities their habitable dimension. Here, signage, furniture and equipment are not isolated elements — they form systems that structure space and reactivate urban life.",[315],{"alt":38,"extension":39,"height":40,"hotspot":38,"type":41,"uid":316,"url":317,"width":44},"551b15b0f369","https://cdn.sanity.io/images/535lnz3g/production/b1998a84bc9b12df33090103a3c5fa77463a3ef8-2000x1333.jpg","Floema Urban — signage, furniture and equipment for urban spaces",{"name":19,"posts":320,"slug":20},[],{"name":22,"posts":322,"slug":23},[],[324,327,330,370],{"_type":325,"title":326,"upperTitle":170},"journalHeader","Exploring ideas, insights, and stories that inspire conversation and shape the future.",{"_type":328,"title":329},"newsletter","Get the latest updates, straight to your inbox",{"_type":331,"featuredCaseStudies":332,"upperTitle":369},"featuredCaseStudy",[333,339,345,351,357,363],{"metadata":334,"presentation":335},{"slug":266},{"category":336,"desc